This paper discusses optimization algorithms commonly used in deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the Adam optimization algorithm, which is widely used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also discusses the stability of the algorithm, which is relevant to the field of neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper provides some rule-of-thumb warmup schedules, which is relevant to the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
